# C++ Driver Rules

- C++17, `rclcpp`, Eigen3. Match existing naming in `roverrobotics_ros2_driver.cpp`.
- Protocol selection is driven by `robot_type` YAML param — add new robots via protocol class + config, not hardcoded branches scattered across files.
- New protocol sources go in `library/librover/src/` and must be listed in `CMakeLists.txt` `add_executable`.
- Prefer extending existing protocol classes (`DifferentialRobot`, `ProProtocolObject`, etc.) over duplicating comm logic.
- Keep odometry, cmd_vel, and TF behavior consistent with existing robots unless explicitly changing one platform.
